{"word":"κληρόω","slug":"κληρόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κληρόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>κλῆρος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to appoint</i> to an office <i>by lot</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <el>αἱρεῖσθαι</el> or <el>χειροτονεῖν</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:—of the lot, <i>to fall on</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>designare</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be appointed by lot</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to cast lots, draw lots</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>;—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> also, <el>κληροῦσθαί τι</el> <i>to have allotted one, obtain by lot</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to allot, assign</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>κλ. ὀμφάν</el> <i>to deliver</i> an oracle, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}